    slug: "how-the-prophet-muhammad-peace-be-upon-him-performed-hajj",
    description: `How the Prophet Muhammad (Peace Be Upon Him) Performed Hajj is an English-language Islamic book that provides a detailed, step-by-step account of the Hajj pilgrimage as it was performed by Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) during his farewell pilgrimage (Hajjat al-Wada') in the year 10 AH (632 CE). This farewell Hajj holds a uniquely important place in Islamic tradition because the Prophet (peace be upon him) explicitly stated during this pilgrimage, "Take from me your rituals of Hajj," indicating that the manner in which he performed the pilgrimage that year represents the definitive and complete model for all Muslims to follow. The book meticulously reconstructs every stage of the Prophet's Hajj based on the authentic hadith narrations, providing readers with the most authoritative and detailed guide available for understanding how the Hajj should be performed according to the Sunnah.

The book draws primarily upon the detailed narrations recorded in the major hadith collections, particularly the extensive account narrated by Jabir ibn Abdillah (may Allah be pleased with him) in Sahih Muslim, which is considered the most comprehensive and authoritative single narration describing the Prophet's Hajj. Additional narrations from Sahih al-Bukhari, the Sunan collections, and the Musnad of Imam Ahmad are used to supplement and corroborate the details. The author presents each hadith with its full chain of narration and scholarly grading, allowing readers to verify the authenticity of every detail. The book follows the chronological order of the Hajj rites as performed by the Prophet, beginning with his entry into the state of ihram at Dhul-Hulayfah, his arrival in Makkah, the tawaf (circumambulation) of the Kaabah, the sai (walking between Safa and Marwah), the journey to Mina, the standing at Arafat, the night at Muzdalifah, the stoning of the Jamarat, the sacrifice, the shaving of the head, the tawaf al-ifadah, and the final tawaf before departure from Makkah.

For each stage of the Hajj, the book provides not only a description of what the Prophet did, but also the specific supplications (duas) that he recited at each location and occasion. These include the talbiyah that he recited continuously during ihram, his duas at the Kaabah, his sermon at Arafat, his prayers at Muzdalifah and Mina, and many other supplications that pilgrims are encouraged to recite. The book also addresses important legal and practical questions that arise from the study of the Prophet's Hajj, such as the ruling on combining prayers during travel, the type of Hajj the Prophet performed (Tamattu' or Qiran), the timing of each ritual, and the common mistakes that pilgrims make. The English translation is clear and precise, and the book includes helpful diagrams and maps where appropriate to illustrate the layout of the pilgrimage sites and the routes between them. This book is an essential reference for anyone planning to perform Hajj, as well as for students of Islamic jurisprudence who want to understand the evidences for the various Hajj rulings.`,
    metaDescription: "How the Prophet Muhammad Performed Hajj details the farewell pilgrimage step by step from authentic hadith. Essential English guide for pilgrims."
