    slug: "how-to-pray",
    description: `How to Pray is an English-language Islamic instructional book that provides a clear, detailed, and comprehensive guide to performing the five daily prayers (salah) correctly according to the Sunnah of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him). The book is designed primarily for new Muslims and young Muslims who are learning to pray for the first time, as well as for parents and teachers who are responsible for teaching children how to perform salah. It also serves as a useful reference for any Muslim who wants to verify that their prayer is being performed correctly or who wants to learn about the specific details and evidences for the various movements and supplications within the prayer.

The book begins with a brief but important introduction to the significance and status of salah within Islam, explaining that it is the second pillar of Islam and the first thing that a person will be asked about on the Day of Judgment. It establishes that the prayer is not merely a physical ritual but a direct spiritual connection between the worshipper and Allah, and that performing it correctly is essential for the prayer to be valid and accepted. The book then proceeds to the practical instruction, which is organized in a step-by-step format that is easy to follow. Each step of the prayer is described in clear English prose, accompanied by the Arabic text and transliteration of every supplication and dhikr that is recited during the prayer, along with the English translation of each recitation.

The book covers the pre-requisites of prayer (shurut al-salah), including cleanliness (taharah), the performance of wudu (ablution) and ghusl (full bath), the covering of the awrah, facing the qiblah, and the timings of the five daily prayers. It then details the essential elements (arkan) of the prayer, including the standing, the recitation of Al-Fatihah, the bowing (ruku'), the prostration (sujud), the sitting between the two prostrations, the final sitting, and the salam. For each element, the book describes the physical position, the words to be recited, and the recommended supplications from the authentic Sunnah. The book also covers the recommended acts (sunnan) of the prayer that the Prophet (peace be upon him) regularly performed, the things that invalidate the prayer, common mistakes that people make during prayer, and special prayers such as the Friday prayer, the funeral prayer, the Tarawih prayer of Ramadan, and the Eid prayers. The step-by-step format is supported by clear diagrams or illustrations where helpful, and each prayer movement is explained in terms that a complete beginner can understand and follow. The book includes evidence from the Quran and hadith for the major rulings, and the overall tone is encouraging and supportive, recognizing that learning to pray properly is a journey that requires patience and practice.`,
    metaDescription: "How to Pray is a step-by-step English guide to performing the five daily salah. Covers wudu, movements, supplications, and common mistakes for beginners."
